      About this item

      • 5MP SUPER HD & STUNNING NIGHT VISION: Capture crystal clear videos day & night with 5MP super HD cameras. The 18pcs infrared LEDs allow you to get high-quality night vision up to 100ft, helping you to protect your property even at night.
      • SMART PERSON/VEHICLE DETECTION Smart PoE IP cameras can identify people and vehicles while minimizing unwanted alerts such as animals or shadows. Cameras can also be configured to specify the type of detection when sending alerts to you. Know what happened simply by glancing at the lock screen.
      • PLUG & PLAY POE SYSTEM: With a single network cable, you can connect each IP camera to Reolink NVR for both power supply and video transmission, making the installation easy enough for DIY enthusiasts and beginners.
      • ENHANCED VIDEO RECORDING: Thanks to the built-in mic of Reolink cameras, the system can pick up ambient sound and help to add another layer of security despite the reliable 24/7 continuous recording.
      • 2-YEAR WARRANTY & LIFE-TIME TECH SUPPORT: Reolink products have a 2-year warranty and lifetime tech support. Feel free to contact Reolink anytime for any questions or problems via Amazon message or email.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        5.0 out of 5 stars Every home should have this.
        Reviewed in the United States on April 2, 2022
        Verified Purchase
        Bought this system, and then bought 2 extra cameras in order to use all 8 channels. Easy setup. Install is as easy or hard as you make it. I ran 3/4 EMT and fished the cat6 through. I believe reolink sells mounts, but I fashioned my own.
        The cameras work great, especially considering the price point. I did have 2 cameras fail about 45 days after installing, but I contacted reolink. They honored their warranty and I had 2 new cameras 2 days later. Just had to foot the bill to return the failed cameras...not a bad deal.
        Only downside I've found to this system is their app. Not the most user friendly thing, but it works.
        All in all, I highly recommend this system to any home or business owner looking for an economical and dependable DIY security solution.

      • Joseph B.
        4.0 out of 5 stars good for the price
        Reviewed in the United States on October 27, 2024
        Verified Purchase
        Got this to replace an old Annke CVI sustem. The image quality is a lot better, and the POE is both easier to install and more robust. Cameras are all metal rather than cheap plastic and the mounts are easier to aim.

        Fairly easy to get running on my local LAN. Worked well with both a monitor attached to the NVR as well as remotely (over the LAN) using Reolink client S/W on my PC. The Local WIFI on my network also worked well with the Reolink App on my Iphone. Be sure to download the complete setup guide, the booklet the come with the system is pretty worthless.

        If you want to remote access either by the internet or cellular connection, you need to read up on the network options with can get pretty complicated. The UID simplifies things but you need to make sure to read the support page "How to Enable UID for Reolink Products". If you don't use UID, then some serious network configuration will be required.

        Setting up motion/subject detection is a trial and error process. It does seem to work fairly well, but can produce false alarms (moths and bugs flying in front camera). The alarm notification by text or email could get to be a bother in that case if it happens a lot.

        One negative is the the included cables are quite thin, cheap and only 60 feet long. The KableDirect (Black/Silver) LAN cables are great, $12/100 feet and are outdoor rated and shielded, which I used instead.

        Another minor issue is that the supplied weatherproof cover for the Ethernet connector can't be used with these better cables, so you will need some kind of junction box to protect them outdoors.
